#Tennessee #Waltz is really a love story to me. We brought it to market in 2014 as a “thank you” to our home state for supporting us from the start.  More importantly (to me), the brand was inspired by the love that my grandparents had for one another. It was truly a “love supreme” that inspires me to this day…a living guide that showed me what real love was about in this life.  The song, “Tennessee Waltz,” was the song that was playing when my Grandfather met my Grandmother…it was their first dance.  Some 65+ years later, I would have my own “Tennessee Waltz” IN Tennessee when I had my first date with the love of my lifetime @lauralandhuber under the Nashville stars.  So, yeah, this brand holds a special place in my heart…so I truly hope you get the chance to enjoy a Tennessee Waltz—and have the best #waltzwednesday of your life.  #crownedheads #cigars 🙏🏼

13 years ago today, I got lost in conversation under the stars, sitting beside the most beautiful creature I’d ever laid eyes on, in a couple of Adirondack chairs (that her father built). At the end of the night, I kissed her, and I was “done.” As soon as we kissed, I immediately knew I was home. That was the best and last first date I’d ever have.  That night was so special to me, that to this day we still remember our “Dating Anniversary” every month, and I even had those chairs tatted on my arm with the date of our first date.  As life has grown busier and crazier over the years, we don’t get nearly enough “dates” these days—but I like to think I’m still courting my beautiful wife…and I know I’m the luckiest man to be able to have that honor.  Happy “Sweet 13” Year Dating Anniversary to my Sweet-Soulmatey @lauralandhuber …I love U 2 the moonflowers & back. ❤️🌛🌼💍⚓️

Happy Mothers Day to my Soulmatey @lauralandhuber …you do so much for so many, yet you still have enough in the tank to always show our daughter only the BEST version of you possible…and because of that, she’s growing into someone amazing.
